tyle%2C%20buying%2080%20vehicles%2C%20jewelry%2C%20clothes%2C%20and%20real%20estate.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Texas%20woman%20will%20spend%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20in%20prison%20after%20stealing%20over%20%24100%20million%20from%20the%20military%20to%20fund%20her%20lavish%20lifestyle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20federal%20judge%20sentenced%20Janet%20Yamanaka%20Mello%2C%2057%2C%20to%20a%20term%20of%2015%20years%20in%20federal%20prison%20last%20week%20on%20five%20counts%20of%20fraud%20and%20five%20counts%20of%20filing%20false%20tax%20returns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMello%20previously%20worked%20as%20an%20employee%20for%20the%20Child%20%26amp%3B%20Youth%20Services%20department%20at%20Fort%20Sam%20Houston%2C%20according%20to%20court%20documents.%20From%202016%20to%202023%2C%20she%20operated%20a%20business%20called%20Child%20Health%20and%20Youth%20Lifelong%20Development%2C%20which%20she%20used%20to%20apply%20for%20grants%20through%20the%20military's%204-H%20partnership%20program%2C%20prosecutors%20said.%20Mello%20was%20in%20charge%20of%20approving%20those%20grants%2C%20which%20were%20meant%20to%20fund%20childcare%20and%20other%20programs%20for%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20Mello's%20business%20had%20the%20%26quot%3Bsole%20purpose%26quot%3B%20of%20receiving%20the%20donations%20that%20she%20%26quot%3Bfraudulently%20secured%20by%20way%20of%20her%20position%20as%20a%20CYS%20financial%20program%20manager.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolice%20say%20Mello%20used%20the%20money%20she%20stole%20to%20buy%2080%20vehicles%2C%20more%20than%201%2C500%20pieces%20of%20jewelry%2C%20clothes%2C%20and%20real%20estate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMello's%20penchant%20for%20extravagance%20is%20what%20brought%20her%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20Lucy%20Tan%2C%20acting%20special%20agent%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20IRS'%20field%20office%20in%20Houston%2C%20said%20in%20the%20statement.%20%26quot%3BWe%20identified%20that%20her%20reported%20income%20was%20well%20below%20the%2