e%20getting%20bail%20in%20the%20high%20courts%20will%20not%20necessarily%20get%20it%2C%20as%20a%20result%20of%20which%2C%20they%20have%20to%20move%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20This%20delay%20compounds%20the%20problem%20of%20those%20who%20are%20facing%20arbitrary%20arrests%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20replying%20to%20a%20question%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20keynote%20address%20during%20the%20'11th%20Annual%20Conference%20of%20the%20Berkeley%20Centre%20on%20Comparative%20Equality%20and%20Anti-Discrimination'.%20The%20question%20was%20on%20the%20arbitrary%20arrests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20questioner%20said%20we%20seem%20to%20live%20in%20a%20society%20where%20one%20acts%20first%20and%20seeks%20forgiveness%20later.%20This%20has%20become%20particularly%20true%20for%20public%20authorities%20acting%20in%20a%20politically%20motivated%20manner%20by%20detaining%20activists%2C%20academics%2C%20journalists%20and%20even%20politicians%2C%20including%20the%20chief%20ministers%20of%20opposition%20parties%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20him%2C%20all%20of%20these%20actions%20are%20taken%20with%20deep%20trust%20in%20the%20face%20of%20justice%20coming%20very%20slowly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20reply%2C%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20been%20constantly%20trying%20to%20convey%20that%20part%20of%20the%20reason%20for%20it%20is%20that%20there%20is%20an%20inherent%20distrust%20in%20the%20institutions%20within%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20important%20that%20we%20learn%20to%20trust%20people%20who%20may%20be%20in%20a%20hierarchical%20legal%20system%2C%20like%20much%20below%2C%20which%20are%20the%20trial%20courts.%20We%20have%20to%20encourage%20trial%20courts%20to%20be%20more%20receptive%20to%20the%20need%20for%20accommodating%20concerns%20of%20people%20who%20are%20seeking%20liberty%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20CJI%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnfortunately%2C%20the%20problem%20today%20is%20this%2C%20that%20we%20look%20at%20any%20grant%20of%20relief%20by%20trial%20judges%20with%20a%20degree%20of%20suspicion.%20That%20means%20that%20the%20trial%20judges%20increasingly%20are%20playing%20it%20safe%2C%20not%20granting%20bail%20on%20important%20issues%20of%20serious%20crimes%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20CJI%2C%20judges%20have%20to%20look%20at%20the%20nitty%20gritties%20and%20see%20the%20fine%20prints%20of%20each%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20(judges)%20have%20to%20have%20a%20sense%20of%20robust%20common%20sense.%20Now%2C%20unless%20we%2C%20therefore%2C%20separate%20the%20grains%20from%20the%20chaff%20in%20criminal%20jurisprudence%2C%20it's%20very%20unlikely%20that%20we%20will%20have%20just%20solutions%20and%20to%20allow%20for%20decision%20makers%20to%20separate%20the%20grain%20from%20the%20chaff%2C%20it's%20important%20that%20we%20also%20place%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20trust%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20that's%20my%20concern%20that%20you%20can't%20render%20courts%20as%20in%20the%20hierarchy%20as%20you%20go%20up%20dysfunctional%2C%20just%20by%20the%20number%20of%20very%20small%20cases%20that%20are%20placed%20before%20us%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20him%2C%20most%20of%20the%20cases%20should%20not%20have%20come%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reason%20why%20we%20are%20prioritising%20bail%20is%20to%20send%20this%20message%20across%20the%20nation%20that%20those%20at%20the%20most%20incipient%20levels%20of%20the%20decision-making%20process%20have%20to%20do%20their%20duties%20without%20this%20feeling%20that.%20I've%20been%20disgusted%20that%20my%20career%20will%20be%20on%20the%20line%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20CJI%20underlined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%2