20wars%2C%20the%20US%20freight%20recession%20is%20reshaping%20the%20industry%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22freight%20truck%20checkpoint%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a3d825aab37011780ae9d6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221061%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESiri%20Stafford%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20freight%20recession%20will%20likely%20remain%20drag%20on%20into%20a%20sixth%20quarter%2C%20according%20to%20AFS%20Logistics.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBankruptcies%20and%20aggressive%20competition%20have%20defined%20the%20industry%20downturn%2C%20the%20firm%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDefaults%20may%20be%20a%20necessary%20catalyst%20to%20cut%20down%20on%20the%20sector's%20oversupply%2C%20AFS'%20Tom%20Nightingale%20suggested.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20end%20in%20sight%20for%20the%20freight%20recession%2C%20and%20the%20downturn%20is%20reshaping%20dynamics%20in%20the%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lack%20of%20certainty%20looms%20over%20experts%20regarding%20when%20the%20trucking%20industry%20could%20recover%20from%20its%20slump%2C%20and%20there%20was%20little%20good%20news%20in%20the%20second%20quarter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20recent%20AFS%20Logistics%20and%20TD%20Cowen%20freight%20index%20report%2C%20truckload%20rate%20per%20mile%20has%20continued%20to%20slip%20this%20year%2C%20and%20the%20trend%20is%20set%20to%20continue%20for%20a%20sixth%20straight%20quarter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20problem%20are%20simple%20economics.%20When%20COVID-era%20consumption%20surged%2C%20trucking%20capacity%20ballooned%20to%20embrace%20it.%20But%20a%20few%20years%20later%2C%20high%20interest%20rates%20have%20pressured%20Americans'%20spending%20habits%2C%20leaving%20the%20industry%20with%20a%20supply-demand%20mismatch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%20you%20have%20more%20capacity%2C%20meaning%20more%20trucks%2C%20more%20drivers%2C%20chasing%20less%20freight%2C%26quot%3B%20AFS%20Logistics%20CEO%20Tom%20Nightingale%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20that%20ultimately%20means%20is%20reduced%20prices%20across%20pretty%20much%20all%20%5Bfreight%5D%20modes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAFS%20tracks%20truckload%2C%20less-than-truckload%2C%20and%20parcel%20modes.%20Each%20segment%20is%20facing%20its%20own%20set%20of%20issue%2C%20Nightingale%20said%2C%20and%20they're%20all%20amplifying%20the%20current%20depressed%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22867b7395-76b8-451e-a07d-d8e58079dce7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBankruptcies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20dominant%20themes%20of%20the%20freight%20recession%20has%20been%20a%20surge%20in%20bankruptcies.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fcarrierok_this-year-88000-carriers-faced-the-tough-activity-7139780831971078144-CLdU%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECarrierOK%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2088%2C000%20carriers%20and%208%2C000%20freight%20brokers%20shut%20down%20their%20operations%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trend%20isn't%20over.%20This%20month%2C%20S%26amp%3BP%20Global%20downgraded%20the%20credit%20rating%20of%20Accuride%2C%20a%20trucking%20parts%20manufacturer.%20Part%20of%20its%20reasoning%20was%20that%20commercial%20trucking%20would%20remain%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faccuride-default-freight-recession-outlook-trucks-consumer-demand-sp-global-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edepressed%20for%20two%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20squeezing%20the%20firm's%20sales%20and%20cash%20flow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20truckload%20carriers%20become%20increasingly%20stressed%2C%20and%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20unable%20to%20service%20their%20interest%20payments%2C%20we%20start%20to%20see%20the%20pace%20of%20bankruptcies%20accelerate%2C%26quot%3B%20Nightingale%20noted%2C%20and%20cited%20this%20as%20a%20